The paper deals with the problem of seeded graph matching, which involves identifying a matching between two graphs based on a small set of pre-matched node pairs. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data mining (cs.DM), computer vision (cs.CV), social networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a new framework for seeded graph matching that employs high order structural information and Personalized PageRank, which are techniques commonly used in these sub-fields. Therefore, it is likely that the paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
